      public void initialize(boolean isHolonomic, @NotNull @NotNull CommandTranslator commandTranslator, boolean crashOnError, @Nullable @Nullable edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.TimedRobot timedRobot, Object... parentObjects)
      Parameters:
      isHolonomic - Is the robot using a holonomic drivetrain? (ex: swerve or mecanum)
      commandTranslator - The command translator to use
      crashOnError - Should the robot crash on error? If this is enabled, and an auto fails to load, the robot will crash. If this is disabled, the robot will skip the invalid auto and continue to the next one.
      parentObjects - Objects that can be used to access other objects annotated with AutoBuilderAccessible.
      timedRobot - The timed robot to use to create the period function for the autos. This can be null if you're running autos completely asynchronously.

    • runAutonomous

      public void runAutonomous(String name, String side, boolean allowRunningNetworkAuto)
      Run an auto with the given name and side. These names should match the names given by getAutonomousNames().

      If the auto is not found with the given side, the code will look for an auto with no side. This means you don't have to perform checks to determine if the auto is sided or not.

      Parameters:
      name - The name of the auto to run.
      side - The side of the robot that the auto will be run on.
      allowRunningNetworkAuto - Weather to allow network autos to be run instead of the selected auto. If a network auto is loaded and this is true, it will be run instead of the selected auto.

    • runAutonomous

      public void runAutonomous(File file, boolean allowRunningNetworkAuto)
      Runs an auto that is located at the given absolute file path.
      Parameters:
      file - The absolute file path of the auto to run.
      allowRunningNetworkAuto - Weather to allow network autos to be run instead of the selected auto. If a network auto is loaded and this is true, it will be run instead of the selected auto.
